        8. A swimming pool in the shape of a cuboid has dimensions 12 meters in length, 5 meters in width, and 3 meters in depth. The interior of the pool, including the bottom and the four walls, needs to be covered with waterproof tiles. If each tile has an area of 0.25 square meters, determine the total number of tiles required to completely cover the poolâ€™s surface.
